@cestella , 
> Would this approach require scans on read in the critical path?

I don't perceive that decoding rowkeys is on any critical path.  You only need to look up Profile by serial number (or hash) in the case of decoding rowkeys.  No?

@ottobackwards , could you please state the latest SHA1 on master to which you've merged?
I ask because I'm going to need to bring up a full dev image, and do `git diff`s against the appropriate point on master, rather than try to walk through 400 files in the PR GUI.  I don't want extraneous patches on master confusing the issue.  Thanks.

Also please state the SHA1 on NiFi (branch master?) that I should be comparing the bundle stuff to.

@mattf-horton In the PR description there is a list of files changed and the reason for them, does that help?

I am going to merge master and resolve conflicts this morning.  I have been doing so daily - or just about.

I will find the commit for the nifi stuff.  I have refactored it quite a bit.
